place.name: CHEDGRAVE
place.gazetteerText: CHEDGRAVE, a parish in Loddon district, Norfolk; on the river Chett, ½ a mile N of Loddon, and 4 SW by W of Reedham r. station. Post town, Loddon, under Norwich. Acres, 1, 432. Real property, £2, 693. Pop., 387. Houses, 85. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £231. Patron, Sir T. B. Proctor, Bart. The church is ancient and good; and has a fine Norman doorway and a low tower. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
